Package com.misc.common.moplaf.solver Description

Provides functions to manage solvers.
  • Generator: a problem that can be handled by a solver, and supporting the following concepts
    • GeneratorVar: a variable, for which the solver will select an (optimal) value
    • GeneratorCons: a constraint, that must be satisfied by the solver
    • GeneratorGoal: a goal, that the solver will try to reach
  • SolutionProvider: a mechanism providing solutions for a given problem (a Generator)
  • SolutionReader: a SolutionProvider, extracting a solution from a file (as produced by some solver, not integrated in the present framework)
  • Solver: an engine, capable of solving a problem (a Generator), and providing Solutions

A Solver will be created for a problem (a Generator), will receive one or several goals (GeneratorGoals).
